				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Jebali</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Intresting, are the recipes one time use? How does they work? Will eventually all the recipes be found and posted on some spoiler site?</div>
			
			<hr />
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
Far as I can tell, recipes are just something your character needs to possess to be able to make stuff.  A spoiler site might know and post what ingredients are needed to forge XYZ armor, and you might have them - but if your particular character hasn't bought or found the recipe - you can't make it.<br />
<br />
I'm sure all the recipes will be found and posted - but it won't help all that much - because by the time you can make the particular item, your character's already found the recipe in-game.  Seems like a fairly workable compromise between gameplay and verisimilitude.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
